abstract: Google’s plan to build a huge digital library remained stalled when a federal judge set a proposed schedule for a lawsuit that could take the case to trial next year.
snippet: Google’s plan to build a huge digital library remained stalled when a federal judge set a proposed schedule for a lawsuit that could take the case to trial next year.
lead_paragraph: Google’s plan to build a huge digital library remained stalled on Thursday when a federal judge set a proposed schedule for a lawsuit against the giant search company that could take the case to trial next year.

headline.main: Judge Sets Schedule in Case Over Google’s Digital Library
